{
  "stem": "10572.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had to do-- we either work in the kitchen or work in the camp university or do whatever or rebuild.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had to rebuild the roads.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it seemed to me that one of the toughest jobs was doing the concrete work of building roads.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And since I didn't know yet how tough I had to be in order to survive in the United States, I picked this and volunteered.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There weren't many volunteers for that, building roads, concrete roads.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had a-- we had a man who was in charge of building roads.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was a former architect from Germany by the name of Herz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And some of the roads were-- kept water after every rain.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was a [INAUDIBLE] in the camp that was saying, you don't need brain to build the roads as long as you have Herz, 'herz' being 'heart.' And there was-- again, there was lots of tension in the camp because of the horrible fears that we had for our beloved ones that we left home.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you became-- because after the war broke out after the first of September, there was a complete cut-off.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had no more communications.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We didn't know if my parents were still there or if they were on their way to Auschwitz or that sort.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "At that time we didn't know about Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Auschwitz didn't exist then, but whatever.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I couldn't stand it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I couldn't sleep at night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I started to realize there was one possibility.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We had good, good friends in Denmark.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "A Danish girl had spent two summers as an exchange student at our house and tried-- she and her husband, who was a pastor, tried to get us out of Germany before the war broke out and didn't succeed.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
